    {
      "id": "cultural_1",
      "type": "cultural_note",
      "title": "Kulturelt hjørne — Cultural Corner",
      "heading": "Greetings in Denmark",
      "content": "Danes typically greet each other with 'hej' in almost all situations — with friends, teachers, shopkeepers, and even doctors. Unlike many other cultures, the formal 'De' (capital D) is rarely used in modern Denmark and may even sound strange to younger Danes. Your teacher will almost certainly ask you to call them by their first name. This reflects a core Danish value: lighed (equality). Everyone, regardless of age or position, is approachable. Don't be surprised if your Danish classmates seem very informal — it is not rudeness, it is culture."
